DNA-binding protein HBbu.
"A phylogenetic analysis of Borrelia burgdorferi sensu lato based on
sequence information from the hbb gene, coding for a histone-like
protein.";
-!- FUNCTION: Histone-like DNA-binding protein which is capable of
    wrapping DNA to stabilize it, and thus to prevent its denaturation
    under extreme environmental conditions (By similarity).
-!- SIMILARITY: Belongs to the bacterial histone-like protein family.
DNA condensation; DNA-binding.
